@dilyanpalauzov I checked this again i think it would not so good idea of using env `BUILDAH_HISTORY` and `--add-history` for `buildah build` since by default `--add-history` is configured as false everywhere. Which we cannot do for `build`, `build` is supposed to keep history so layers can be re-used.

I think `--add-history` was added explicitly for `run` purpose so one could commit history with images if they need to. @nalind @rhatdan Could you confirm please.

Could i suggest a new option `--remove-history` which when configured will not write history while building image. However i am still unsure if its practically solving any thing. Since `history` is merely few bytes or mb.
